  <slide>
    <title>Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1</title>
    <contents>

      <p>
        <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG" target="_specification">Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1</a>
      </p>

      <details>
        <summary>Important Features</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>Technology agnostic</li>
          <li>Understanding requires knowledge of features of specific technologies</li>
          <li>Techniques are <strong>not</strong> normative or comprehensive</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/quickref/" target="_specification">How to Meet WCAG 2.1</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/WAI/WCAG21/Understanding/" target="_specification">Understanding WCAG 2.1</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG20-TECHS" target="_specification">Techniques for WCAG 2.1</a></li>
        </ul>
      </details>

      <iframe src="https://www.w3.org/tr/wcag" width="99%" height="600px" title="W3C WCAG 2.1 Guidelines"></iframe>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>Accessible Rich Internet Applications (ARIA) Specification</title>
    <contents>

      <p>
        <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria" target="_specification">Accessible Rich Internet Applications Specification</a>
      </p>

      <details>
        <summary>Important Features</summary>
        <ul>
          <li><code>role</code> semantics</li>
          <li>Accessible name</li>
          <li>Accessible description</li>
          <li>States and properties</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/accname" target="_specification">W3C Accessible Name and Description Computation Specification</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/core-aam/" target="_specification">W3C Core Accessibility API Mappings</a></li>
        </ul>
      </details>

      <iframe src="https://www.w3.org/tr/wai-aria" width="99%" height="600px" title="W3C ARIA Specfication"></iframe>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>ARIA Authoring Practices</title>
    <contents>

      <p>
        <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-practices" target="_specification">W3C ARIA Authoring Practices</a>
      </p>

      <details>
        <summary>Important Features</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>Design patterns for using landmarks and creating accessible widgets</li>
          <li>Full working and reviewed examples</li>
          <li>Review of accessible name and description alogithms</li>
        </ul>
      </details>

      <iframe src="https://www.w3.org/tr/wai-aria-practices" width="99%" height="600px" title="W3C ARIA Authoring Practices"></iframe>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>HTML 5</title>
    <contents>
      <p>
        <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/#the-html-element" target="_specification">HTML 5 Specification</a>
      </p>

      <details>
        <summary>Important Features</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>Default <code>role</code> semantics</li>
          <li><code>role</code> semantics restrictions</li>
          <li>Built in features to support accessibility</li>
          <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html-aria/" target="_specification">W3C ARIA in HTML</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html-aam" target="_specification">HTML Accessibility API Mappings Specification</a></li>
        </ul>
      </details>


      <iframe src="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/#the-html-element" width="99%" height="600px" title="W3C HTML 5 Specification"></iframe>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>HTML 5: main element</title>
    <contents>
      <p>
        <a href="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/#the-main-element" target="_specification">HTML 5: main element</a>
      </p>

      <details>
        <summary>Accessibility Feature</summary>
        <ul>
          <li>Supports implementation of WCAG Success Criteria 2.4.1 Bypass Blocks</li>
          <li>Identifies the main content of the page</li>
          <li>Creates a <code>main</code> landmark on the page for screen readers</li>
          <li>Can be use for the target of a skip to main link</li>
        </ul>
      </details>

      <iframe src="https://www.w3.org/TR/html5/#the-main-element" width="99%" height="600px" title="W3C MAIN element Specification"></iframe>
    </contents>
  </slide>

